Tom Ince’s England future is in serious doubt after he and dad Paul took the decision to snub a place at the Under-21 European Championships this summer.

Boss Gareth Southgate has warned his former England team-mate of the consequences of his son turning his back on the Three Lions.

Ince Snr – England’s first black captain – has told Southgate they want to concentrate on Tom’s club career rather than represent his country in Czech Republic. 

