And Ince had hoped for promotion to Hodgson’s full squad after his appearance at the Euros.

‘I’ve had two great years at Under-21 level and my ambition now is to try to push for the senior team,’ he said in September.

‘Playing for a club in the Premier League and the exposure that comes with that will hopefully provide me with the pathway to do it. ‘You can see at the minute Roy Hodgson is giving a lot of young players from the Under-21s and Premier League clubs a chance. I hope I can get that opportunity – although it doesn’t mean I don’t appreciate playing for the Under-21s at major tournaments.’

